<div class="markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><p data-start="0" data-end="107">Yes, exactly! The <strong data-start="18" data-end="56">TLB (Translation Lookaside Buffer)</strong> is a <strong data-start="62" data-end="85">fast, cached lookup</strong> for the page table.</p><h3 data-start="109" data-end="137"><strong data-start="113" data-end="135">Why is TLB needed?</strong></h3><ul data-start="138" data-end="399"><li data-start="138" data-end="234">The <strong data-start="144" data-end="158">page table</strong> is stored in <strong data-start="172" data-end="187">main memory</strong>, making memory address translation <strong data-start="223" data-end="231">slow</strong>.</li><li data-start="235" data-end="399">Every memory access requires <strong data-start="266" data-end="273">two</strong> memory accesses:<ol data-start="295" data-end="399"><li data-start="295" data-end="336"><strong data-start="298" data-end="326">Lookup in the page table</strong> (slow).</li><li data-start="339" data-end="399"><strong data-start="342" data-end="367">Fetch the actual data</strong> (slower due to extra lookup).</li></ol></li></ul><h3 data-start="401" data-end="425"><strong data-start="405" data-end="423">How TLB helps?</strong></h3><ul data-start="426" data-end="743"><li data-start="426" data-end="523"><strong data-start="428" data-end="464">TLB is a small, high-speed cache</strong> that stores recently used <strong data-start="491" data-end="520">page table entries (PTEs)</strong>.</li><li data-start="524" data-end="619">If a <strong data-start="531" data-end="550">virtual address</strong> has a valid mapping in TLB (<strong data-start="579" data-end="590">TLB hit</strong>), translation is <strong data-start="608" data-end="616">fast</strong>.</li><li data-start="620" data-end="743">If a <strong data-start="627" data-end="639">TLB miss</strong> occurs, the page table in memory is accessed, and the result is <strong data-start="704" data-end="725">cached in the TLB</strong> for future use.</li></ul><h3 data-start="745" data-end="763"><strong data-start="749" data-end="761">Analogy:</strong></h3><p data-start="764" data-end="919" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Think of <strong data-start="773" data-end="796">TLB as a speed dial</strong> for addresses—if a number (address) is frequently dialed, you don’t need to go through the full contact list (page table).</p></div>